2025-05-13 14:35:30,895 INFO: Chat message received. Session data: {'_fresh': False, 'company_desc': 'coal mining', 'conversation_history': ['Q: esrs', 'A: <p><strong>ESRS Requirements for Mining, Quarrying, and Coal Sector</strong></p>\n<h3><strong>Environmental Disclosures</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Spills and Incidents</strong><ul>\n<li>Total number of significant spills, volume by substance, and definition of "significant spill" (ESRS E2-28)</li>\n<li>Number of overall significant incidents, including those involving hazardous materials and waste management (ESRS E2-30)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Biodiversity and Ecosystems</strong><ul>\n<li>Average direct land use change in hectares (ESRS E2-67a)</li>\n<li>Percentage of land-use change area rehabilitated/restored, including in protected and key biodiversity areas (ESRS E2-67b)</li>\n<li>Metrics on state of species (ESRS E2-67c)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Health and Safety Disclosures</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Hazards Exposure</strong><ul>\n<li>List of Substances of Very High Concern (SVHCs) for chemical hazards (ESRS S1-29a)</li>\n<li>List of key physical or ergonomic hazards and their inclusion in the health and safety management system (ESRS S1-29b)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Health and Safety Metrics</strong><ul>\n<li>Work-related fatalities, injuries, and recordable ill health, broken down by employees and non-employees (ESRS S1-31)</li>\n<li>Average hours of training per worker on health, safety, and emergency preparedness (ESRS S1-32)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Social Disclosures</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Own Workforce</strong><ul>\n<li>Policies, actions, and targets addressing housing facilities, access to basic services, recreational facilities, and social spaces for workers (ESRS S1-MQC.69a)</li>\n<li>Policies, actions, and targets addressing working time and work-life balance for round-the-clock or remote operations (ESRS S1-MQC.69b)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Work Stoppages</strong><ul>\n<li>Number of work stoppages, including number of employees involved and duration (MQC 7-70)</li>\n<li>Actions taken to resolve major work stoppages (MQC 7-72)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>', 'Q: esrs', 'A: <p><strong>ESRS Requirements for Mining, Quarrying, and Coal Sector</strong></p>\n<h3><strong>Environmental Disclosures</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Spills and Incidents</strong><ul>\n<li>Total number of significant spills, volume by substance, and definition of "significant spill" (ESRS E2-28)</li>\n<li>Number of overall significant incidents, including those involving hazardous materials and waste management (ESRS E2-30)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Biodiversity and Ecosystems</strong><ul>\n<li>Average direct land use change in hectares (ESRS E2-67a)</li>\n<li>Percentage of land-use change area rehabilitated/restored, including in protected and key biodiversity areas (ESRS E2-67b)</li>\n<li>Metrics on state of species (ESRS E2-67c)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Health and Safety Disclosures</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Hazards Exposure</strong><ul>\n<li>List of Substances of Very High Concern (SVHCs) for chemical hazards (ESRS S1-29a)</li>\n<li>List of key physical or ergonomic hazards and their inclusion in the health and safety management system (ESRS S1-29b)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Health and Safety Metrics</strong><ul>\n<li>Work-related fatalities, injuries, and recordable ill health, broken down by employees and non-employees (ESRS S1-31)</li>\n<li>Average hours of training per worker on health, safety, and emergency preparedness (ESRS S1-32)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Social Disclosures</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Own Workforce</strong><ul>\n<li>Policies, actions, and targets addressing housing facilities, access to basic services, recreational facilities, and social spaces for workers (ESRS S1-MQC.69a)</li>\n<li>Policies, actions, and targets addressing working time and work-life balance for round-the-clock or remote operations (ESRS S1-MQC.69b)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Work Stoppages</strong><ul>\n<li>Number of work stoppages, including number of employees involved and duration (MQC 7-70)</li>\n<li>Actions taken to resolve major work stoppages (MQC 7-72)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>', 'Q: special disclosures for mqc', 'A: <p><strong>Special Disclosures for MQC (Mining, Quarrying, and Coal) Sector under ESRS</strong></p>\n<h3><strong>MQC Specific Disclosures</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>MQC 11. Transparency about Contracts and Licenses</strong><ul>\n<li>Whether contracts/licenses are publicly available and where found</li>\n<li>Reason for non-public availability and plans/timetable for publication (if applicable)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>MQC 12. State-Aid and Competition</strong><ul>\n<li>Notifications, investigations, proceedings, or commitments related to antitrust violations or state aid</li>\n<li>Outcomes of legal proceedings (sanctions, fines, etc.)</li>\n<li>Total state aid received by country</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>MQC 13. Beneficial Ownership</strong><ul>\n<li>Information on beneficial ownership structure</li>\n<li>Methodology for identifying beneficial owners</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>MQC 14. Oil and Gas Purchased from States</strong><ul>\n<li>Details on ongoing transactions generating revenue for states (directly or through third parties)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Additional Relevant Disclosures from Context</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Closure of Assets (MQC 4)</strong><ul>\n<li>List of material sites with rehabilitation/restoration plans</li>\n<li>Involvement of affected communities and employees in post-closure planning</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Training on Health, Safety, and Emergency Preparedness</strong><ul>\n<li>Average hours of training per worker, broken down by employees and non-employees</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Other Sector-Specific Disclosures (Referenced for Completeness)</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Environmental</strong><ul>\n<li>Spills and incidents (ESRS E2-28, E2-30)</li>\n<li>Biodiversity and ecosystems metrics (ESRS E2-67a, E2-67b, E2-67c)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Health and Safety</strong><ul>\n<li>Hazards exposure (ESRS S1-29a, S1-29b)</li>\n<li>Health and safety metrics (ESRS S1-31, S1-32)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Social</strong><ul>\n<li>Policies for own workforce (ESRS S1-MQC.69a, S1-MQC.69b)</li>\n<li>Work stoppages (MQC 7-70, MQC 7-72)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>', 'Q: special disclosures for mqc', 'A: <p><strong>Special Disclosures for MQC (Mining, Quarrying, and Coal) Sector under ESRS</strong></p>\n<h3><strong>MQC Specific Disclosures</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>MQC 11. Transparency about Contracts and Licenses</strong><ul>\n<li>Whether contracts/licenses are publicly available and where found</li>\n<li>Reason for non-public availability and plans/timetable for publication (if applicable)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>MQC 12. State-Aid and Competition</strong><ul>\n<li>Notifications, investigations, proceedings, or commitments related to antitrust violations or state aid</li>\n<li>Outcomes of legal proceedings (sanctions, fines, etc.)</li>\n<li>Total state aid received by country</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>MQC 13. Beneficial Ownership</strong><ul>\n<li>Information on beneficial ownership structure</li>\n<li>Methodology for identifying beneficial owners</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>MQC 14. Oil and Gas Purchased from States</strong><ul>\n<li>Details on ongoing transactions generating revenue for states (directly or through third parties)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Additional Relevant Disclosures from Context</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Closure of Assets (MQC 4)</strong><ul>\n<li>List of material sites with rehabilitation/restoration plans</li>\n<li>Involvement of affected communities and employees in post-closure planning</li>\n</ul>\n</